GEVC, Barrister (Dr.) Taiwo Afolabi was a recipient of the prestigious Heritage For Life Foundation Award for his philanthropic gestures towards the Nigerian society. The award ceremony which was held at the Muson Centre, Onikan, Lagos had in attendance eminent personalities such as Lady Maiden Alex Ibru- Publisher, Guardian Newspaper; Christopher Kolade, former British High Commissioner and many more. Middle: Tobi Afolabi, Executive Director, Ports & Cargo Handling Services Limited receiving the special recognition award from Chief Emeka Anyaoku, former Secretary General of the Commonwealth on behalf of Barr. (Dr.) Taiwo Afolabi, Group Executive Vice Chairman, SIFAX Group while Captain Ibraheem Olugbade, Executive Director, SIFAX Off Dock looks on.